When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message for this repository, use exactly this subject format:

{taskType}#{number}-{branchName}-{details}

Parts:
- taskType: issue (bug fix), feature (new capability), or enhancement (improvement) — lowercase
- number: issue/ticket number from the branch (e.g. branch 7-mapbox → 7)
- branchName: current git branch name
- details: short phrase describing what changed (not a file list)

Rules:
- Single subject line only. No conventional commits prefix. No body unless explicitly requested.
- Infer taskType from the staged changes.
- Read number from the leading digits of the branch name when present.

Examples:
- enhancement#7-7-mapbox-add frontend nvmrc for lts/krypton
- issue#7-7-mapbox-fix mapbox token not loading on public report page
- feature#7-7-mapbox-add draggable location picker to public report flow
